        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "LLM-as-judge uses a capable language model to evaluate the outputs of other models (or itself), replacing or augmenting human annotation. The quality of the evaluation depends critically on how the judge is set up: which model, which prompt structure, which output format, and how the judge's decisions are calibrated against human preferences."
          }
