      {
        "type": "blockquote",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Never use the model being evaluated as its own judge in a production pipeline. LLMs exhibit strong self-preference bias: they consistently rate their own outputs as better than equally good or better outputs from other models. Pandia et al. 2022 measured this at 10\u201315pp bias for GPT-series models."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
