        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Absolute Scoring: Pointwise Judge Setup"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A pointwise judge assigns a score to a single model response. The prompt structure consists of four parts:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Role declaration.",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " Establish the judge's role and authority. \"You are an expert evaluator for AI assistant responses.\""
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Evaluation criteria.",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " Specify what to assess: accuracy, helpfulness, harmlessness, conciseness, etc."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Scoring rubric.",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " Anchor descriptions for each scale point to reduce ambiguity and variance."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Output format.",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " Require structured output (JSON) to enable automated parsing without regex fragility."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "POINTWISE_JUDGE_SYSTEM = '''You are an expert evaluator for AI assistant responses.\nAssess the response on the following criteria:\n  - Accuracy: factually correct and not misleading\n  - Completeness: addresses all aspects of the question\n  - Clarity: well-organised, easy to understand\n  - Conciseness: no unnecessary padding or repetition\n\nScore from 1 to 5 using these anchors:\n  1 - Very poor: inaccurate or harmful; fails to address the question\n  2 - Poor: mostly unhelpful with significant gaps or errors\n  3 - Acceptable: addresses the question but with notable weaknesses\n  4 - Good: helpful and accurate with minor weaknesses\n  5 - Excellent: accurate, complete, clear, and well-paced\n\nOutput JSON only: {\"score\": <1-5>, \"reason\": \"<one sentence>\"}'''\n\nPOINTWISE_JUDGE_USER = '''Question: {question}\n\nResponse to evaluate:\n{response}'''\n\nfrom openai import OpenAI\nimport json\n\nclient = OpenAI()\n\ndef judge_pointwise(question: str, response: str) -> dict:\n    msg = client.chat.completions.create(\n        model='gpt-4o',\n        messages=[\n            {'role': 'system', 'content': POINTWISE_JUDGE_SYSTEM},\n            {'role': 'user', 'content': POINTWISE_JUDGE_USER.format(\n                question=question, response=response\n            )},\n        ],\n        response_format={'type': 'json_object'},\n        temperature=0,\n    )\n    return json.loads(msg.choices[0].message.content)\n\nresult = judge_pointwise(\n    question='What is the time complexity of binary search?',\n    response='Binary search runs in O(log n) time because each step halves the search space.',\n)\nprint(result)  # {'score': 5, 'reason': 'Accurate, complete, and concise.'}"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Pairwise Comparison: Relative Judge Setup"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A pairwise judge compares two responses to the same question and outputs which is better (or a tie). This is the approach used by MT-Bench, Chatbot Arena, and AlpacaEval. The prompt structure:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "PAIRWISE_JUDGE_SYSTEM = '''You are an expert evaluator comparing two AI assistant responses.\nYour task is to determine which response is better.\nCriteria (in order of importance):\n  1. Accuracy: correct information, no fabrication\n  2. Helpfulness: genuinely addresses the user's need\n  3. Clarity: well-organised and easy to follow\n  4. Conciseness: no filler or padding\n\nOutput JSON only:\n{\"winner\": \"A\" | \"B\" | \"tie\", \"reason\": \"<one sentence explaining the key difference>\"}\n\nDo not let response length affect your verdict \u2014 a concise, accurate response\nbeats a verbose but padded one.'''\n\nPAIRWISE_JUDGE_USER = '''Question: {question}\n\n[Response A]\n{response_a}\n\n[Response B]\n{response_b}'''\n\ndef judge_pairwise(\n    question: str,\n    response_a: str,\n    response_b: str,\n) -> dict:\n    msg = client.chat.completions.create(\n        model='gpt-4o',\n        messages=[\n            {'role': 'system', 'content': PAIRWISE_JUDGE_SYSTEM},\n            {'role': 'user', 'content': PAIRWISE_JUDGE_USER.format(\n                question=question,\n                response_a=response_a,\n                response_b=response_b,\n            )},\n        ],\n        response_format={'type': 'json_object'},\n        temperature=0,\n    )\n    return json.loads(msg.choices[0].message.content)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Position bias: the judge tends to prefer whichever response appears first (\"A\"). Always run each pair in both orders and aggregate:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "def judge_pairwise_debiased(\n    question: str,\n    response_1: str,\n    response_2: str,\n) -> dict:\n    \"\"\"Run in both orders to cancel position bias.\"\"\"\n    # Order 1: 1=A, 2=B\n    r1 = judge_pairwise(question, response_1, response_2)\n    # Order 2: 2=A, 1=B (swapped)\n    r2 = judge_pairwise(question, response_2, response_1)\n\n    # Translate order-2 winner back to response numbering\n    flip = {'A': 'B', 'B': 'A', 'tie': 'tie'}\n    winner_order1 = r1['winner']   # 'A'=resp_1, 'B'=resp_2\n    winner_order2 = flip[r2['winner']]  # flipped: 'A'=resp_1, 'B'=resp_2\n\n    if winner_order1 == winner_order2:\n        consensus = winner_order1   # both agree\n    else:\n        consensus = 'tie'           # position-biased disagreement\n    return {\n        'winner': consensus,\n        'order1': r1,\n        'order2': r2,\n        'position_bias_detected': winner_order1 != winner_order2,\n    }"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
