        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "REFERENCE_BASED_SYSTEM = '''You are evaluating an AI assistant's response.\nA reference (correct) answer is provided.\nCompare the response against the reference. Score 1\u20135:\n  5: All key facts from the reference are correct and present\n  4: Most key facts correct; minor omission or imprecision\n  3: Some key facts correct; notable gaps or errors\n  2: Mostly incorrect or missing key facts\n  1: Completely wrong or contradicts the reference\nOutput: {\"score\": <1-5>, \"missing_facts\": [<list>], \"wrong_facts\": [<list>]}'''\n\nREFERENCE_BASED_USER = '''Question: {question}\nReference answer: {reference}\nModel response: {response}'''"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Chain-of-Thought Reasoning in the Judge"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Requiring the judge to produce reasoning before its verdict improves reliability: the model is less likely to output an inconsistent score when it has first articulated why one response is better. This is the \"reason before score\" pattern:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "COT_JUDGE_SYSTEM = '''You are an expert evaluator.\nEvaluate the response to the question below.\n\nFirst, in 2-3 sentences, identify the main strengths and weaknesses.\nThen output your score (1-5) and a one-sentence summary.\n\nFormat your output as JSON:\n{\n  \"analysis\": \"<2-3 sentence analysis>\",\n  \"score\": <1-5>,\n  \"reason\": \"<one sentence>\"\n}'\n'''\n\n# Studies (Wang et al. 2023) show CoT judges achieve:\n# - Higher agreement with human labels (\u03ba improves ~0.05-0.10)\n# - Lower variance across repeated runs (same input, same score)\n# - Better calibration at the extremes (1 and 5) where judges\n#   are most uncertain without reasoning"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "blockquote",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Always require reasoning before the score, not after. A score followed by a justification is often post-hoc rationalization. A justification followed by a score forces the model to commit its reasoning before the verdict, producing more consistent and interpretable evaluations."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Structured Output and Parsing"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Judge outputs must be parsed programmatically. The most reliable approach is JSON mode (where the model is constrained to valid JSON output) combined with a response schema:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from pydantic import BaseModel, Field\nfrom openai import OpenAI\n\nclient = OpenAI()\n\nclass JudgeOutput(BaseModel):\n    analysis: str = Field(description='2-3 sentence analysis of strengths/weaknesses')\n    score: int = Field(ge=1, le=5, description='Overall quality score 1-5')\n    reason: str = Field(description='One-sentence verdict summary')\n\ndef judge_structured(\n    question: str,\n    response: str,\n    system_prompt: str,\n) -> JudgeOutput:\n    msg = client.beta.chat.completions.parse(\n        model='gpt-4o-2024-08-06',\n        messages=[\n            {'role': 'system', 'content': system_prompt},\n            {'role': 'user', 'content': f'Question: {question}\\n\\nResponse: {response}'},\n        ],\n        response_format=JudgeOutput,\n        temperature=0,\n    )\n    return msg.choices[0].message.parsed\n\nresult = judge_structured(\n    question='Explain what a p-value is.',\n    response='A p-value is the probability of observing results at least this extreme if the null hypothesis is true.',\n    system_prompt=COT_JUDGE_SYSTEM,\n)\nprint(result.score, result.reason)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Temperature and Consistency"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Always use temperature=0 for judge calls in production. Higher temperatures introduce random variation in verdicts that is indistinguishable from real quality differences between model outputs:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import numpy as np\n\ndef judge_variance_test(\n    question: str,\n    response: str,\n    n_runs: int = 10,\n    temperature: float = 0.0,\n) -> dict:\n    \"\"\"Measure score variance across repeated judge calls.\"\"\"\n    scores = []\n    for _ in range(n_runs):\n        msg = client.chat.completions.create(\n            model='gpt-4o',\n            messages=[\n                {'role': 'system', 'content': POINTWISE_JUDGE_SYSTEM},\n                {'role': 'user', 'content': f'Question: {question}\\nResponse: {response}'},\n            ],\n            response_format={'type': 'json_object'},\n            temperature=temperature,\n        )\n        scores.append(json.loads(msg.choices[0].message.content)['score'])\n    return {\n        'mean': np.mean(scores),\n        'std': np.std(scores),\n        'range': (min(scores), max(scores)),\n        'temperature': temperature,\n    }\n\n# Expected results:\n# temperature=0.0: std ~ 0.0-0.1, range same score\n# temperature=0.7: std ~ 0.5-1.0, range may span 3 points"
          }
